PREREQUISITES FOR RECOVERY
---------------------------
1. age secret key (password manager: one-line AGE-SECRET-KEY-1...)
   - Needed ONLY for curlbin backups (service configs)
   - NOT needed for vzdump restores from this USB drive
2. Ansible Vault password (macOS Keychain: ansible-vault-master)
3. SSH key (Secretive / Secure Enclave)
4. Internet access (for curlbin service config backups + git clone)
5. This repository: git clone the infrastructure-automation repo

SCENARIO 1: NVMe DIED — FULL PROXMOX REBUILD
----------------------------------------------
1. Boot Proxmox installer (download from proxmox.com or use a saved ISO)
2. Install Proxmox VE on replacement NVMe
   - Use same network config: check current/etc-pve/ for reference
3. Mount this USB drive:
     mkdir -p /mnt/usb && mount /dev/sdX1 /mnt/usb
4. Restore network configuration:
     cp /mnt/usb/current/etc-pve/nodes/{{ ansible_hostname }}/network /etc/network/interfaces
     ifreload -a
5. Restore /etc/pve/ configuration:
     CAUTION: /etc/pve/ uses pmxcfs (cluster filesystem).
     Consult official Proxmox docs for the correct restore procedure.
     A naive cp may not work. Typically:
     - Copy storage.cfg, user.cfg, datacenter.cfg individually
     - Copy VM/CT configs from nodes/{{ ansible_hostname }}/qemu-server/ and lxc/
6. Import ZFS pools (if data disks survived):
     zpool import -f <poolname>
7. Restore VMs and LXCs from vzdump snapshots:
   NOTE: LXC restores require --storage local-zfs (local dir doesn't support rootdir)
{% for host in groups['all'] %}
{% if hostvars[host].vm_id is defined and not hostvars[host].archived | default(false) %}
     qmrestore /mnt/usb/current/{{ hostvars[host].vm_id }}/vzdump-qemu-{{ hostvars[host].vm_id }}-*.vma.zst {{ hostvars[host].vm_id }}
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
{% for host in groups['all'] %}
{% if hostvars[host].container_id is defined and not hostvars[host].archived | default(false) %}
     pct restore {{ hostvars[host].container_id }} /mnt/usb/current/{{ hostvars[host].container_id }}/vzdump-lxc-{{ hostvars[host].container_id }}-*.tar.zst --storage local-zfs
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
8. Start VMs/LXCs in order:
   a. OPNsense FIRST (provides networking for everything else)
   b. Then remaining containers
9. Run Ansible to restore monitoring, backup crons, and scripts:
     ansible-playbook ansible/playbooks/site.yml --limit {{ inventory_hostname }}
10. Reconfigure vzdump schedule (not Ansible-managed):
      Datacenter > Backup > Add job
      Schedule: daily 03:00
      Guests: {% for host in groups['all'] %}{% if hostvars[host].vm_id is defined and not hostvars[host].archived | default(false) %}{{ hostvars[host].vm_id }}{% if not loop.last %},{% endif %}{% endif %}{% endfor %}{% for host in groups['all'] %}{% if hostvars[host].container_id is defined and not hostvars[host].archived | default(false) %},{{ hostvars[host].container_id }}{% endif %}{% endfor %}

      Compression: zstd, Retention: keep-daily=15, Storage: local

SCENARIO 2: VM/LXC CORRUPTION (NVMe OK)
-----------------------------------------
Restore a single guest from this USB drive:
  mount /dev/sdX1 /mnt/usb
{% for host in groups['all'] %}
{% if hostvars[host].vm_id is defined and not hostvars[host].archived | default(false) %}
  qmrestore /mnt/usb/current/{{ hostvars[host].vm_id }}/vzdump-qemu-{{ hostvars[host].vm_id }}-*.vma.zst {{ hostvars[host].vm_id }} --force 1
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
{% for host in groups['all'] %}
{% if hostvars[host].container_id is defined and not hostvars[host].archived | default(false) %}
  pct restore {{ hostvars[host].container_id }} /mnt/usb/current/{{ hostvars[host].container_id }}/vzdump-lxc-{{ hostvars[host].container_id }}-*.tar.zst --force
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}

SCENARIO 3: SERVICE CONFIG ONLY (VM/LXC OK)
---------------------------------------------
Service configs are backed up daily to curlbin (encrypted with age).
URLs are posted to Slack on each backup run.

To decrypt a curlbin backup:
  curl -o backup.age "https://{{ curlbin_host }}/FILE_ID"
  age --decrypt -i key.txt -o backup.tar.gz backup.age
  tar -xzf backup.tar.gz

See docs/BACKUP_AND_RECOVERY.md for per-service restore procedures.

VERIFYING FILE INTEGRITY
--------------------------
Check the MANIFEST.txt in current/ for file sizes and MD5 checksums.
Compare with: md5sum /mnt/usb/current/<id>/vzdump-*

